{"ID":270309, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"309\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs308.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs310.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 309<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Many men will say, &ldquo;I will never forsake you,<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> but will stand by you<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> at all times.&rdquo;  But the\n  moment you teach them<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> some of the mysteries of the kingdom of God<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> that are retained in the\n  heavens<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and are to be revealed to the children of men<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> when they are prepared for them they will\n  be the first to stone you<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> and put you to death.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> It was this same principle that crucified the Lord\n  Jesus Christ, and will cause the people to kill the prophets in this generation.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Many things are insoluble to the children of men<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> in the last days: for instance, that God should\n  raise the dead,<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> and forgetting that things have been hid from before the foundation of the world,<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span>\n  which are to be revealed to babes in the last days.<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span><\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Some Men &ldquo;Too Wise to Be Taught&rdquo;<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">There are a great many wise men and women too in our midst who are too wise to be taught;<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span>\n  therefore they must die in their ignorance,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> and in the resurrection they will find their mistake.<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span>\n  Many seal up the door of heaven<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> by saying, So far God may reveal and I will believe.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">All men who become heirs of God and joint heirs with Jesus Christ<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> will have to receive the\n  fulness of the ordinances<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> of his kingdom; and those who will not receive all the ordinances<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> will\n  come short<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> of the fullness of that glory,<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> if they do not lose the whole.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Paradise<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">I will say something about the spirits in prison.<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> There has been much said by modern divines\n  about the words of Jesus (when on the cross) to the thief, saying, &ldquo;This day shalt thou be with me\n  in paradise.&rdquo;<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> King James&rsquo; translators make it out to say paradise. But what is paradise? It is a\n  modern word: it does not answer at all to the original word that Jesus made use of. Find the original\n  of the word paradise. You may as easily find a needle in a haymow. Here is a chance for battle, ye\n  learned men. There is nothing in the original word in Greek from which this was taken that signifies\n  paradise; but it was&mdash;This day thou shalt be with me in the world of spirits:<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> then I will teach you\n  all about it and answer your inquiries. And Peter says he went and preached to the world of spirits\n  (spirits in prison, 1 Peter, 3rd chap. 19th verse),<span class=\"footRef\">25<\/span> so that they who would receive it could have it\n  answered by proxy by those who live on the earth,<span class=\"footRef\">26<\/span> etc.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108257\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108257)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108257)\">Matt. 26:33-35<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110332\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110332)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110332)\">Heb. 13:5<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113149\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113149)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113149)\">D&amp;C 6:18<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115745\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115745)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115745)\">D&amp;C 121:9<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115928\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115928)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115928)\">D&amp;C 124:16<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108702\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108702)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108702)\">John 6:60-67<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108484\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108484)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108484)\">Luke 8:10<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"115436\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 115436)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(115436)\">D&amp;C 107:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116428\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116428)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116428)\">D&amp;C 132:46<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111272\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111272)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111272)\">2 Ne. 27:11<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"114264\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 